  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Bui-Donga Smallholder Integrated Sheep and Goat Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Farmers</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will be located in Cameroon&#x2019;s Northwest region and will cover communities in the Bui and Donga/Mantung Divisions. The major socio-economic challenge in this region is food insecurity; mostly in the rural areas where low protein intake, poor households and highest HIV and AIDS rates the country prevail. Heifer will provide 870 resource-limited farm families&#x2014;174 original and 696 who will benefit from passing on the gift&#x2014;with 4,350 sheep and goats. The animals will help improve their livelihoods through enhanced household food security and nutrition, increased income and also mitigate the effects of HIV and AIDS. Families will receive training on Heifer&#x2019;s 12 cornerstones, group development and management; gender equity, HIV and AIDS issues, improved animal and crop husbandry, integrated crop-livestock techniques, market gardening, post-harvest management and more. They will receive related agricultural materials/supplies and other inputs to enable them build up production assets. Heifer will also ensure that at least 60 percent of direct beneficiaries in this project are women and disadvantaged persons.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&quot;Train farmers on Heifer&#x2019;s 12 cornerstones, group development and management, improved animal and crop husbandry, integrated crop-livestock techniques, market gardening and post-harvest. Sensitize assisted farm families on HIV and AIDS issues. Facilitate access to agricultural materials/supplies.&quot;</narrative>
  </description>
